  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Probabilistic analysis provides a distribution of possible outcomes rather than a single worst-case value, allowing for a more nuanced understanding of system performance and reliability.Davis et al. [51] categorize SPTA methods based on the sources of probabilistic behavior they account for, and explains how each category contributes to determining the WCET.",
    "These three categories are SPTA based on Probabilities from Inputs, SPTA based on Probabilities from Faults, and SPTA based on Probabilities from Random Replacement Caches.SPTA based on probabilities from inputs analyzes the probability distributions of input values and their impact on execution paths.",
    "By understanding how different inputs affect execution times, the method estimates the likelihood of various execution times.",
    "For instance, certain inputs might lead to longer execution paths more frequently, which is captured in the WCET analysis.",
    "Laurent et al. [52] present a method for determining probabilistic distributions of task execution times using static analysis."
  ],
